Surface common Postgres integration and DBM setup issues through `datadog-agent diagnose`. The check now ships explicit pre-flight diagnostics covering connection/auth, Postgres version, `shared_preload_libraries`, `track_activity_query_size`, `track_io_timing`, `pg_stat_statements.max`, `pg_monitor` role, `datadog` schema, `pg_stat_statements` extension + readability, and the `datadog.explain_statement` function. Existing runtime warnings recorded via `record_warning` are also mirrored into the diagnose output, so agent status and `agent diagnose` stay in sync. Diagnostics that read `GUC_SUPERUSER_ONLY` settings (such as `shared_preload_libraries`) now emit a warning pointing at `pg_monitor` when the underlying row is hidden from the datadog user, instead of silently skipping.
